## Phase 1 — Data Architecture Refactoring

**Goal:** Eliminate flat files. Define canonical bilingual chunk format. No vector DB yet — chunks stored as structured JSON in `data/chunks/`. Retriever falls back to cosine similarity over TF-IDF vectors (still a major upgrade over keyword scan).

### 1.1 Seed Data Migration

`faculties.txt` + `faculties_ar.txt` → two ChunkDocuments:

```json
{
  "id": "chunk_fac_industry_001",
  "content": {
    "en": "Faculty of Industry and Energy Technology — Departments: Information Technology, Textile Technology, Food Technology, Tractor and Agricultural Machinery, Medical Device Technology, Railway Technology.",
    "ar": "كلية تكنولوجيا الصناعة والطاقة — الأقسام: تكنولوجيا المعلومات، الغزل والنسيج، تكنولوجيا الأغذية، الجرارات والمعدات الزراعية، تكنولوجيا الأجهزة الطبية، تكنولوجيا السكك الحديدية."
  },
  "metadata": {
    "type": "faculty",
    "source": "faculties_seed_v1",
    "language": "bilingual",
    "domain": "faculty",
    "subCategory": "industry_energy",
    "ttl": 86400,
    "updatedAt": "2026-04-29T00:00:00Z"
  }
}
```

Each FAQ entry in `faq.json` also becomes a ChunkDocument with `type: "faq"` and `ttl: 604800` (7 days).

### 1.2 Chunking Rules

| Content Type | Target Chunk Size | Overlap |
|---|---|---|
| Faculty description | 150–250 tokens | none |
| Course syllabus | 200–350 tokens | 50 tokens |
| FAQ entry | 1 Q+A pair | none |
| Policy document | 200 tokens | 80 tokens |
| Event | 1 event per chunk | none |

Chunks must not split mid-sentence. Use `tiktoken` (via `@dqbd/tiktoken`) to count tokens.

### 1.3 New File: `src/data/ChunkLoader.ts`

```typescript
import { ChunkDocument } from '../types/Chunk';
import fs from 'fs';
import path from 'path';
import { v4 as uuidv4 } from 'uuid';

export class ChunkLoader {
  private chunksDir: string;

  constructor() {
    this.chunksDir = path.join(process.cwd(), 'data', 'chunks');
    if (!fs.existsSync(this.chunksDir)) {
      fs.mkdirSync(this.chunksDir, { recursive: true });
    }
  }

  public loadAll(): ChunkDocument[] {
    const files = fs.readdirSync(this.chunksDir).filter(f => f.endsWith('.json'));
    return files.flatMap(f => {
      const raw = fs.readFileSync(path.join(this.chunksDir, f), 'utf-8');
      return JSON.parse(raw) as ChunkDocument[];
    });
  }

  public save(chunks: ChunkDocument[]): void {
    const file = path.join(this.chunksDir, `chunks_${Date.now()}.json`);
    fs.writeFileSync(file, JSON.stringify(chunks, null, 2));
  }
}
```

