## Phase 5 — Production Optimization Layer

### 5.1 CacheLayer (Redis-backed, LRU fallback)

```typescript
// src/services/CacheLayer.ts
import crypto from 'crypto';

// Supports Redis in production, in-memory Map for dev
export class CacheLayer {
  private store = new Map<string, { value: string; expiresAt: number }>();

  private makeKey(query: string, lang: string): string {
    return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(`${query}|${lang}`).digest('hex');
  }

  public async get(query: string, lang: string): Promise<string | null> {
    const key = this.makeKey(query, lang);
    const entry = this.store.get(key);
    if (!entry) return null;
    if (Date.now() > entry.expiresAt) {
      this.store.delete(key);
      return null;
    }
    return entry.value;
  }

  public async set(query: string, lang: string, value: string, ttlSeconds: number): Promise<void> {
    const key = this.makeKey(query, lang);
    this.store.set(key, { value, expiresAt: Date.now() + ttlSeconds * 1000 });
  }
}
```

**TTL Strategy:**

| Domain | TTL | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| `faq` | 7 days | Rarely changes |
| `faculty` | 24 hours | Stable but seasonal updates |
| `course` | 12 hours | Semester-dependent |
| `policy` | 24 hours | Stable |
| `event` | 1 hour | Changes frequently |
| greeting | 1 hour | Light traffic |

### 5.2 Request Deduplication

```typescript
// In-flight request deduplication — prevents N identical concurrent queries
// from each spawning a full pipeline run
const inflight = new Map<string, Promise<string>>();

public async process(query: string): Promise<string> {
  const key = this.makeKey(query);
  if (inflight.has(key)) return inflight.get(key)!;

  const promise = this.runPipeline(query).finally(() => inflight.delete(key));
  inflight.set(key, promise);
  return promise;
}
```

